<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n08184l"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n08" href="#n08184l">N08 (VI.B.6)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n08all.htm#n08184l"> 184(l)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Iona <font color="green">[ate seals]</font> &mdash;</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">There is a characteristic story of a thief who used to row across to an islet frequented by seals which the monks <font color="green">[of Iona]</font> regarded as their property and, like the poacher, used for food. &ldquo;Why do you steal?&rdquo; asked the saint. &ldquo;When you are in want, come to us.&rdquo; And he ordered a sheep to be killed and given, that the unlucky man might not go home empty-handed. <small> Stephen Gwynn, <a name="SGHI" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#SGHI"><cite title="source">The History of Ireland</cite></a> (1923) 39</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
